  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-our-singing-voice ,
    oakcurric:thread-practising-and-preparing-for-a-performance .

oakcurric:unit-2662
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Singing together: how songs unite us"@en ;
  curric:slug "singing-together-how-songs-unite-us" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit investigates the power of music to unite people. Pupils explore how song
  is used in sacred spaces, sports arenas and live concerts. Pupils study songs with unity
  as their common theme and use the lyrics to guide an effective, emotive performance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Prior to this unit, pupils have studied songs sung for a range of
  purposes, including songs that evoke a feeling, work songs, community songs, and songs that
  tell a story. Pupils now start to explore the concept of being united through songs. Building
  on their knowledge of songs changing over time, there is an increased focus on conveying
  meaning and mood through song, which is explored further in later units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2662-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2662-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2662-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2662-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2662-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2662-6 ;
  curric:id "2662"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.890138Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-music-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-our-singing-voice ,
    oakcurric:thread-music-over-time-and-in-different-places ,
    oakcurric:thread-practising-and-preparing-for-a-performance ,
    oakcurric:thread-notating-and-sharing-music .

oakcurric:unit-2668
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Singing together: music that comments on social change"@en ;
  curric:slug "singing-together-how-songs-have-the-power-for-change" ;
  rdfs:comment "TBA"@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their vocal performance skills, in this unit pupils are
  encouraged to consider the intention of the lyricist in order to convey meaning. Pupils
  utilise prior learning of varying dynamics and vocal timbre for effect as well as deepening
  their learning of what makes an effective vocal ensemble. We build pupils' understanding of
  texture and structure and develop their proficiency for part singing. Pupils continue to
  reflect on our question of why we sing, considering the purpose of song in this context and
  previous units in which we have explored the meaning of song.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2668-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2668-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2668-3 ,
